{
  "_comment": [
    "Explicit lookup tables for shape-variant image selection.",
    "",
    "top: matched on (component_box, normalized pillar_front, normalized pillar_back, elephant).",
    "Normalization: each of the 4 comma-separated positions in a pillar_config becomes",
    "'0' if it's exactly zero, otherwise 'x' (pillar SIZE, 1 vs 2, does not change which",
    "image is used, only whether a pillar is present at that position does). e.g. 1,0,0,1 and",
    "2,0,0,2 both normalize to x,0,0,x. All-zero (0,0,0,0) is its own distinct pattern.",
    "See image_selector.py:_normalize_pillar_pattern().",
    "",
    "elephant (yes/no) replaces the earlier altar-depth-vs-box-depth comparison entirely.",
    "",
    "As of the latest rule chart, only component_box top1_bottom1 and top2_bottom2 (and only",
    "when elephant=no) have rows for BOTH front patterns (x,0,0,x and 0,0,0,0); every other",
    "box/elephant combination only has a row for front=x,0,0,x. A request that lands on a",
    "combo with no matching row (e.g. front=0,0,0,0 on top1_bottom2, or any 0,0,0,0-front row",
    "with elephant=yes) falls through to the naming-convention guess / default image \u2014 this is",
    "expected, not a bug, unless a future rule chart adds that row explicitly.",
    "",
    "side_cutting: matched on (component_box, level_count) exactly as given on the chart.",
    "",
    "middle_cutting: matched on level_count only (no component_box concept here).",
    "",
    "Any combo not listed in any table falls back to a naming-convention/formula guess,",
    "and then to the template default image if that is missing too.",
    "",
    "SHARED 'output_mappings_by_image' table (top-level key below): since the same",
    "image is reused across multiple variants that share identical variables, the",
    "output_mappings (Excel cell addresses) are defined ONCE per unique image name,",
    "not repeated per row. resolve_output_mappings() (image_selector.py) matches a",
    "row the normal way, then looks up that row's own \"image\" value in this shared",
    "table. A row MAY still carry its own inline \"output_mappings\" to override the",
    "shared table for that one exact variant (rare \u2014 only if a variant needs to",
    "differ despite sharing an image), which takes priority over the shared lookup.",
    "If neither exists, resolution falls back to the template's static default in",
    "templates.json \u2014 unchanged prior behavior for variants with no mapping yet.",
    "PLACEHOLDER NOTE: the 'top_image0.png' and 'top_image6.png' entries below are",
    "illustrative placeholders demonstrating the mechanism only \u2014 their cell",
    "addresses are NOT confirmed against the real rule chart yet and must be",
    "verified/replaced before relying on them, same as middle_cutting's TODO cells",
    "in templates.json."
  ],
